                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 636,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "An effect with the sonic trait functions only if it makes sound, meaning it has no effect in an area of silence or in a vacuum. This is different from an auditory spell, which is effective only if the target can hear it. A sonic effect might deal sonic damage. A creature with this trait has a magical connection to powerful sound.",
